  "prompt": "As an old-ish person, how do you feel when you hear a young person curse 'blindly'?",
  "response": "Feelings towards young people cursing can vary greatly depending on personal perspective and cultural background. \n\nSome older individuals might feel concerned, disappointed, or uncomfortable when they hear young people using foul language, especially if they believe it shows a lack of respect or maturity. They may worry about the changing norms and the potential impact on interpersonal relationships and societal standards.\n\nOn the other hand, some older people might be more understanding or indifferent, recognizing that language and expressions evolve over time. They may see cursing as a form of self-expression or a way for young people to fit in with their peers.\n\nUltimately, it's a personal reaction, and there isn't a universally right or wrong way to feel about it. Communication between generations about language use and its impact can often lead to better understanding and respect.",
